# Ordering Service

## Architecture

- Follow Clean Architecture: `Ordering.API` → `Ordering.Application` → `Ordering.Core` ← `Ordering.Infrastructure`.
- Use CQRS via `Common.Mediator` — add commands/queries in `Ordering.Application`, handlers alongside, register via assembly scan in `ServiceRegistration.cs`.
- Use Mapperly `OrderMapper` for entity/DTO/event mapping; do not add AutoMapper.
- Keep MassTransit consumers in `Ordering.API/EventBusConsumer/` — they should delegate to mediator commands, not contain business logic.

## Messaging & contracts

- Primary checkout path is RabbitMQ: `BasketOrderingConsumer` on `basketcheckout-queue`, `BasketOrderingConsumerV2` on `basketcheckout-queue-v2`.
- Queue names come from `Infrastructure/EventBus.Messages/Common/EventBusConstant.cs` — do not hardcode queue strings.
- Activity consumers (`ProductActivityConsumer`, `OrderActivityConsumer`) must check `ExistsByEventIdAsync` before insert for idempotency.
- Only v1 basket consumer and HTTP test checkout publish `OrderActivityEvent`; v2 consumer does not.

## Data & persistence

- EF Core context is `OrderContext` in `Ordering.Infrastructure/Data/`; migrations live in `Ordering.Infrastructure/Migrations/`.
- Register new repositories in `InfraServices.AddInfraServices` and implement against `RepositoryBase<T>`.
- Audit fields (`CreatedBy`, `LastModifiedBy`) are set in `OrderContext.SaveChangesAsync` — currently hardcoded to `"slowey"`.

## API & routing

- `OrderController` route is `/api/v1/Order` (inherits versioned route from `ApiController`).
- `ActivityController` uses fixed `/api/v1/Activity` — different routing pattern from Order.
- Ocelot gateway config references `/api/v1/Ordering` — verify gateway paths if changing controller names.

## Do not

- Do not treat `POST /api/v1/Order` as the production checkout path — it is marked for testing only.
- Do not skip FluentValidation when adding new commands — validators auto-register from assembly.
- Do not add authentication assumptions — no auth scheme is configured in `Program.cs`.

